Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Developer* role with *CAI*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, backend system design, and AI integration, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *expertise in Java, Spring Boot, SQL, and the development of scalable applications and Web APIs*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent system using LangChain and LangGraph that translates natural-language intents into validated *Web API* calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed workflows. To ensure system stability and performance, I built generative code solutions (API-aware templates and SDK patterns) and implemented an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing and structured logs. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using *Python*, *PostgreSQL (SQL)*, and *Redis* for efficient data processing across AWS S3 and Google Cloud Storage. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with *Java*, *Spring Boot*, and *MVC* patterns, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, and developed backend workflows using *AWS Step Functions* and *PowerShell* to automate data import jobs and maintain source materials in *GitHub* — both of which required *systems-level thinking and operational stability focus*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *assist in designing and developing customized solutions, supporting client needs, and ensuring system performance* and drive impact within an agile engineering team at CAI.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *values of collaboration and taking ownership to deliver impactful technology solutions*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA and PyTorch on an HPC cluster. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops and *systems training* on building AI Agents for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring *the role of conducting systems training and workshops to empower both staff and clients*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *CAI and its mission to empower individuals and organizations through technology*.

I have always been passionate about *uniting talent and technology to power the possible for communities* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *creating a future where every person can live at the peak of possible through inclusive and innovative solutions*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

